    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style and culture of the historical section of the coast of the Gulf of Guinea in Africa extending approximately from Axim, Ghana, or nearby Cape Three Points, in the west to the Volta River in the east.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stijl en cultuur uit het historische deel van de kust van de Golf van Guinee in Afrika, dat zich ongeveer uitstrekt van Axim (Ghana) of het nabijgelegen Cape Three Points in het westen tot aan de rivier de Volta in het oosten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>歷史上的非洲幾內亞灣海岸地區之風格與文化，範圍大約自西邊的阿克西姆、迦納或附近的三尖角(Cape Three Points)，延伸至東邊的沃爾特河。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
